		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">The Blank Slate</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div class="dablink">For other uses, see <a href="/wiki/Blank_slate_(disambiguation)" title="Blank slate (disambiguation)">Blank slate (disambiguation)</a>.</div>
<p><i><b>The Blank Slate: The Modern Denial of Human Nature</b></i> is a best-selling 2002 book by <a href="/wiki/Steven_Pinker" title="Steven Pinker">Steven Pinker</a> arguing against <a href="/wiki/Tabula_rasa" title="Tabula rasa">tabula rasa</a> models of the <a href="/wiki/Social_science" title="Social science" class="mw-redirect">social sciences</a>. Pinker argues that human behavior is substantially shaped by <a href="/wiki/Evolutionary_psychology" title="Evolutionary psychology">evolutionary psychological</a> adaptations. The book was nominated for the 2003 <a href="/wiki/Aventis_Prize" title="Aventis Prize" class="mw-redirect">Aventis Prizes</a> and was a finalist for the <a href="/wiki/Pulitzer_Prize" title="Pulitzer Prize">Pulitzer Prize</a>.</p>
